├── storage/
├── tests/
└── vendor/
```

---

## 🔐 Authentication Flow

RoomHub uses a **dual-token strategy** — a short-lived access token + a refresh token stored in the `refresh_tokens` table.

```
Register ──► RoleService (assign role) ──► RegisterService ──► token pair returned
Login    ──► LoginService ──► access_token + refresh_token
Refresh  ──► RefreshTokenRequest ──► RefreshController ──► new access_token
Logout   ──► revoke token ──► delete refresh_token
```

---

## 🛣️ API Routes (`routes/api.php`)

### Auth — Public Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Controller | Description |
|--------|----------|------------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/register` | `RegisterController` | Register new user |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | `LoginController` | Login with email & password |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/refresh` | `RefreshController` | Refresh access token |
| `POST` | `/api/auth/forgot-password` | `ForgotPasswordController` | Send OTP to phone/email |
| `PUT` | `/api/auth/forgot-password` | `ForgotPasswordController` | Reset password with OTP |

### Auth — Protected Routes (Sanctum)

| Method | Endpoint | Controller | Description |
|--------|----------|------------|-------------|
| `POST` | `/api/auth/logout` | `LoginController` | Logout & revoke token |
| `PUT` | `/api/auth/register` | `RegisterController` | Update user profile |

---

## 📦 Request Validation Classes

| Request Class | Validates |
|---------------|-----------|
| `RegisterStoreRequest` | name, email, phone, password, password_confirmation |
| `RegisterUpdateRequest` | name, phone, avatar (profile update) |
| `LoginStoreRequest` | email, password |
| `LoginUpdateRequest` | (logout / token revoke) |
| `RefreshTokenRequest` | refresh_token |
| `ForgotPasswordStoreRequest` | phone or email (send OTP) |
| `ForgotPasswordUpdateRequest` | otp_code, password, password_confirmation |

---

## ⚙️ Services

### `LoginService.php`
- Validates credentials
- Issues Sanctum access token
- Creates refresh token record
- Handles logout & token revocation

### `RegisterService.php`
- Creates new `User` record
- Hashes password
- Triggers role assignment via `RoleService`
- Returns token pair on success

### `RoleService.php`
- Assigns `landlord` or `tenant` role to user
- Can be called after registration or role-selection step

---

## 🗄️ Models

### `User.php`
```
id, name, email, phone, password, role, is_active,
avatar, provider, provider_id,
email_verified_at, remember_token, timestamps
```

### `RefreshToken.php`
```
id, user_id, token (hashed), expires_at, timestamps
```

---

## 🚀 Setup & Installation

### Requirements
- PHP >= 8.3
- Composer
- MySQL
- Node.js (for `node_modules` — likely used for asset building)

### Steps

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/roomhub-backend.git
cd roomhub-backend

# 2. Install PHP dependencies
composer install

# 3. Copy environment file
cp .env.example .env

# 4. Generate application key
php artisan key:generate

# 5. Configure .env
DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=roomhub
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=

# 6. Run migrations
php artisan migrate

# 7. (Optional) Run seeders
php artisan db:seed

# 8. Start development server
php artisan serve
# → http://localhost:8000
```

---

## 🧪 Testing

```bash
# Run all tests
php artisan test

# Run specific test suite
php artisan test --testsuite=Feature
php artisan test --testsuite=Unit
```

Test files are located in the `tests/` directory.

